\par 
\par \hich\af32\dbch\af16\loch\f32 Ballack: The totally classic way: by playing boldly and well. And by being a role model to young players off the field.
\par 
\par \hich\af32\dbch\af16\loch\f32 SPIEGEL:\hich\af32\dbch\af16\loch\f32  Is it bells and whistles when the team management and psychologist refer to the European Championship as a "mountain hike?" They've even come up with a separate logo for it.
\par 
\par \hich\af32\dbch\af16\loch\f32 Ballack: Well, one man's encouragement is another's bells and whistles. We recei\hich\af32\dbch\af16\loch\f32 
ved a little folder with something about the team's goals. Let's put it this way: It's something that provides guidance but is not paramount. A mountain hike means that it'll be a difficult path. This sort of thing is helpful to some people, but less so t
\hich\af32\dbch\af16\loch\f32 o\hich\af32\dbch\af16\loch\f32  others. I have nothing against psychologists. But I've been playing football since I was six years old, and didn\hich\f32 \rquote \loch\f32 
t grow up with that kind of attention. When I was 10 and wasn't playing well, the trainer chewed me out. That's all. I played well again in t\hich\af32\dbch\af16\loch\f32 h\hich\af32\dbch\af16\loch\f32 e next match.
